I've got this guy completely
wrapped around my finger.

33:55.773 --> 33:58.193
He'd do anything for me.

33:58.235 --> 34:00.279
And most of the time,
he's got me working with him.

34:00.362 --> 34:02.156
Kind of low-level shit,
just helping out.

34:02.197 --> 34:05.576
But I can get away from him plenty.
I got all kinds of reasons.

34:05.660 --> 34:09.121
I've sketched half the place
already. I've copied a lot of keys.

34:09.205 --> 34:12.376
I can get you access to basically
any room in the place.

34:12.460 --> 34:14.003
Where's the scepter?

34:14.045 --> 34:16.964
Well, see, that's the kink.

34:17.047 --> 34:18.591
Now, get this.

34:18.675 --> 34:21.594
It was arranged to be
brought into the country...

34:21.678 --> 34:25.683
inside the leg
of an antique piano.

34:25.725 --> 34:29.521
And it was so simple.
Then they impounded it.

34:29.562 --> 34:31.563
I mean, can you guess why?

34:31.606 --> 34:34.443
Fucking bugs.

34:34.525 --> 34:38.031
I mean, the whole shipment
was contaminated with termites.

34:38.114 --> 34:40.074
Asian longhorn beetles.

34:41.159 --> 34:43.078
We got fucked by bugs.

34:45.539 --> 34:47.041
These things
burrow into the wood...

34:47.123 --> 34:49.002
so they were in the crates
of most of the shipment.

34:49.085 --> 34:51.545
So they took the goods out
and delivered most of them.

34:51.630 --> 34:54.424
But the piano is made of wood too,
so they impounded it.

34:54.507 --> 34:56.677
They took the whole thing
and put it in quarantine.

34:56.760 --> 34:59.388
Medium security,
third-floor lockup.

34:59.430 --> 35:01.015
They're really scared
of these things...

35:01.098 --> 35:02.768
and they can't send
them back to France.

35:05.437 --> 35:07.606
So they decided
to burn everything.

35:16.659 --> 35:18.619
Now, I'll tell ya...

35:18.661 --> 35:20.997
I didn't know which one of the
fucking legs this thing is in...

35:21.080 --> 35:24.209
but half of me was tempted to grab
them all and make a break for it.

35:24.292 --> 35:28.131
I mean, I don't know if this
thing's gonna melt or what.

35:29.298 --> 35:31.467
I mean, I was dying.

35:35.013 --> 35:37.349
I had to improvise a little.

35:42.063 --> 35:44.423
- I-I saw something in the fire.
- We're just burning stuff.

35:44.441 --> 35:48.654
No. Look, look.
I saw something in the...

35:48.737 --> 35:52.074
Piano. In the piano,
I saw a... Look.

35:52.157 --> 35:53.243
- I saw something.
- Jack!

35:54.619 --> 35:56.747
There! There!

35:58.916 --> 36:00.835
What is it?

36:10.471 --> 36:12.139
So everybody's freaking out.

36:12.181 --> 36:14.267
Nobody knows what this is
or what to do with it.

36:14.350 --> 36:16.310
They don't see this kind
of excitement down there.

36:16.352 --> 36:18.354
So they call some supervisor.
They get him out of bed.

36:18.438 --> 36:20.858
He comes down,
he takes one look at this thing.

36:20.942 --> 36:24.070
He doesn't know what the hell it is,
but he knows it's worth a lot.

36:24.153 --> 36:27.157
He tells them, until they can
sort it out, put it in the basement.

36:27.949 --> 36:30.076
- And that's what they do.
- Don't worry. Don't worry.

36:30.118 --> 36:32.622
- Don't worry about it.
- I want to see, Danny.

36:32.705 --> 36:35.416
- Can I see?
- No. Come on. Let's go now.

36:35.458 --> 36:37.919
Okay. Bye-bye. Bye.

36:53.395 --> 36:55.022
The basement
in the customshouse...

36:55.105 --> 36:57.401
is the most secure lockup
in eastern Canada.

36:57.484 --> 36:59.903
It was built as a bomb shelter
during the Cold War.

36:59.987 --> 37:03.449
All their important stuff's there...
state's evidence, narcotics...

37:03.532 --> 37:05.284
confiscated weapons.

37:05.326 --> 37:08.120
That scepter is in a safe
somewhere in this room.

37:08.162 --> 37:10.207
But the thing is,
there's no... there's no cameras.

37:10.290 --> 37:12.960
If there was, I would've seen
an angle on the video monitors.

37:13.043 --> 37:16.714
So if we can put you inside that
room, you can work on it all night.

37:18.883 --> 37:22.429
We'll need pictures of the safe
or a model number from their files.

37:22.512 --> 37:25.850
Then we're gonna need plans...
infrastructure maps...

37:25.933 --> 37:29.103
blueprints, schematics,
anything we can get our hands on.

37:29.187 --> 37:31.064
That's all I got for now,
but give me two days.

37:31.147 --> 37:33.608
We just gotta find a way
to get into that basement.

38:16.075 --> 38:18.202
You gonna let it go, or are we gonna
drive around pissed all night?

38:18.286 --> 38:19.954
Why don't you kiss my ass?

38:44.733 --> 38:48.278
- We're about set up. You ready?
- Hold on.

39:05.089 --> 39:07.885
- Wanna give me a mark?
- Not yet. Not yet.

39:20.775 --> 39:22.485
How you doing?

39:22.568 --> 39:25.029
Stay off the air until I call.

39:49.015 --> 39:51.393
Three-three, two-six...

39:51.476 --> 39:53.854
two-nine, three-two.

39:53.896 --> 39:59.570
I repeat: 33, 26, 29, 32.

39:59.653 --> 40:03.741
Copy that. Three-three, two-six,
two-nine, three-two.

40:07.787 --> 40:11.542
Make a right.
Proceed east about 20 yards.

40:11.625 --> 40:13.544
You should see
the next opening.

40:22.179 --> 40:24.557
I'm at a wall here,
a cinder block wall...

40:24.640 --> 40:26.434
where you told me I have to go.

40:26.517 --> 40:28.798
Are you sure about that?
It shows a straight shot on here.

40:28.853 --> 40:31.481
It's not my imagination.
I'm right here in front of it.

40:31.564 --> 40:33.942
You wanna come down here
and see for yourself?

40:35.403 --> 40:38.239
Right. Okay, okay. Hold on.

40:40.575 --> 40:42.494
All right,
just give me a second.

40:45.330 --> 40:48.251
- Can you read me?
- Make a left. Go about 20 feet.

40:48.293 --> 40:49.878
You should run
into a parallel tunnel.

40:49.961 --> 40:52.422
Make a right. You'll be
right back on course.

40:56.135 --> 40:58.929
Take the tunnel
about 150yards due west.

40:58.971 --> 41:01.266
You'll reach a "T" junction.
Tell me when you're there.

41:01.350 --> 41:02.768
About 300yards.

41:02.851 --> 41:05.729
- Came to the end. Made a right.
- Head Northwest.

41:05.771 --> 41:07.565
Northeast.
Check that. Northeast.

41:07.606 --> 41:09.108
One second. Hold on.

41:10.151 --> 41:13.237
- Are you with me?
- Going west. Going west.

41:13.321 --> 41:18.119
- I'm going west. I'm in a circle.
- Make a right. Go 40yards east.

41:18.160 --> 41:22.123
Then make a left turn.
Go about...

41:22.206 --> 41:24.250
Make a right. Head back.

41:24.292 --> 41:26.754
You got maybe 500 yards to go.

41:34.012 --> 41:37.349
Straight ahead 20 feet, and you
should be dead under the room.

41:37.432 --> 41:39.018
The tunnel will keep on going.

41:39.102 --> 41:41.521
But look up.
You should see the access ladder.

41:48.111 --> 41:50.113
I'm at a shaft.
I'm gonna climb up.

42:02.336 --> 42:04.255
What are you doing?

42:05.007 --> 42:06.383
Still climbing.

42:27.365 --> 42:28.283
This looks like it.

44:02.351 --> 44:04.269
I'm done.

44:16.242 --> 44:18.160
What the hell is this?

44:23.958 --> 44:26.128
Hey, you got a utility crew
all over the entrance.

44:26.212 --> 44:28.130
You're gonna have to find
another way out.

45:02.419 --> 45:04.548
Where are you?

45:11.514 --> 45:13.891
I'm at De La Montagne
and Ottawa.

45:13.975 --> 45:15.977
Repeat:
De La Montagne and Ottawa.

45:16.018 --> 45:17.980
Got it. We're on our way.

45:24.821 --> 45:26.739
This should be it, right here.

45:27.991 --> 45:30.870
We're here.
I'm just trying to find you.

45:30.953 --> 45:33.372
There. He's right over there.

45:55.732 --> 45:57.526
Okay, you're all clear.

45:57.567 --> 45:59.528
I'm coming out.

46:43.912 --> 46:45.330
Hello.

46:46.958 --> 46:48.918
Anybody home?

47:07.982 --> 47:10.234
- Champagne.
- Yeah.

47:10.317 --> 47:12.487
- Nice touch.
- Nice dress.

47:12.571 --> 47:14.406
You like? Thank you.

47:16.742 --> 47:21.414
So, you asked me a question
a couple of days ago.

47:21.497 --> 47:23.958
And you gave it
some serious thought?

47:24.918 --> 47:26.837
Actually,
I forgot the question.

47:29.298 --> 47:31.801
Here's my answer.

47:31.884 --> 47:33.386
You're not holding up
your glass.

47:33.469 --> 47:34.804
I'm sorry.

47:37.098 --> 47:39.811
My father was a lawyer...
very smart man...

47:39.894 --> 47:43.231
and he would always say
that a deal is only good...

47:43.314 --> 47:47.152
if it leaves both parties feeling
as if they gave up something.

47:47.194 --> 47:50.405
Is an answer coming soon?
'Cause the glass is getting heavy.

47:52.492 --> 47:53.910
Okay.

47:55.078 --> 47:57.205
I will change my life...

47:57.289 --> 47:59.208
I will move here...

48:01.043 --> 48:02.378
I will love you...

48:04.047 --> 48:08.177
and believe that this is
the best decision that I've made.

48:09.928 --> 48:12.973
But I will not move here
if it means that one day...

48:13.057 --> 48:14.767
I might have to talk
to you through glass.

48:14.850 --> 48:17.271
I won't move here if it means
spending my nights worrying.

48:17.354 --> 48:22.902
So if you can promise me, as of
right now, that you're through...

48:24.153 --> 48:27.198
then we can drink
to making changes.

48:35.583 --> 48:38.545
I... I said you could drink now.

48:38.586 --> 48:39.671
I know.

48:39.754 --> 48:42.300
I wanna do all that.

48:43.926 --> 48:48.223
I just have to tell you
that I'm gonna do one more thing...

48:48.264 --> 48:50.392
- and that's it.
- Oh, fuck.

48:50.433 --> 48:52.936
Everything you said is great.
It's perfect.

48:52.978 --> 48:56.274
I just have one more thing
I have to do.

48:56.358 --> 48:59.027
You put that out there when you
knew you couldn't follow through.

48:59.111 --> 49:01.947
I put it out there because...
I am following through.

49:01.989 --> 49:03.949
- This is my last one. I promise.
- Sure it is.

49:04.032 --> 49:06.076
I promise you
it is my last one.

49:06.118 --> 49:08.789
Then quit. Quit now.

49:08.872 --> 49:11.959
- What does "one last one" mean?
- It means we don't need anything.

49:12.042 --> 49:15.921
I didn't need anything before,
and I don't need anything now...

49:15.963 --> 49:18.215
but what I wanted
was to be with you.

49:18.299 --> 49:21.845
And what I didn't need was exactly
this kind of painful bullshit.

49:21.929 --> 49:26.475
My life wasn't perfect before,
but at least we were clear.

49:29.228 --> 49:30.229
Give me some...

49:32.524 --> 49:34.485
I'll see you when I see you.

50:45.567 --> 50:47.861
Hey, what are you doing?

50:47.944 --> 50:50.698
Somebody put fingerprints
on my window, Danny.

50:50.782 --> 50:54.035
- You don't need to do it.
- I like a clean window, Danny.

50:54.119 --> 50:55.328
It's all right.

50:55.412 --> 50:58.582
We missed you last night.
You feeling better?

50:58.665 --> 51:00.125
- Yes, thank you.
- Sure?

51:00.209 --> 51:01.449
Yes, I'm okay.
Thank you, Danny.

51:01.502 --> 51:05.132
- Take your time. Okay, bye-bye.
- Bye-bye.

51:05.215 --> 51:06.299
Bye.

51:23.361 --> 51:25.279
That's your safe.

51:30.494 --> 51:33.581
Traeger standing jeweler's safe,
this year's model.

51:33.664 --> 51:36.918
If it's new, it's gonna be tough
to get the schematics.

51:37.001 --> 51:39.003
I've got all this year's books.

51:39.045 --> 51:41.465
- Really?
- Yeah. What else?

51:41.549 --> 51:44.802
Okay, the system's
Ironclad Security.

51:44.886 --> 51:46.513
They're a big commercial
industrial outfit.

51:46.554 --> 51:48.890
They handle a lot
of the government buildings here.

51:48.932 --> 51:52.060
Now, this building's pretty old.
The lines are all over the place.

51:52.144 --> 51:55.148
They're easy to find. I can cut in
three or four different places...

51:55.231 --> 51:58.944
and let you in from there, but I
need the engineering pass codes.

51:59.027 --> 52:00.570
I've been looking.
They don't keep them in here.

52:00.654 --> 52:03.991
They'll be at Ironclad.
I don't know what to do.

52:04.074 --> 52:05.367
Okay.

52:07.036 --> 52:08.955
What, are you
calling someone now?

52:13.210 --> 52:16.005
- What? Who is this?
- It's me. Turn down the music.

52:18.758 --> 52:21.011
Hey, Nick, I am fucked up.

52:21.095 --> 52:23.430
My mother's totally
out of control.

52:23.514 --> 52:25.141
Listen. Listen carefully.

52:25.224 --> 52:26.892
Ironclad Security.

52:26.976 --> 52:29.020
- Big outfit.
- Yeah.

52:29.103 --> 52:31.606
I need engineering pass codes
for the customshouse.

52:31.689 --> 52:33.734
I don't know, man.
My concentration's shot.

52:33.776 --> 52:37.071
I haven't slept in, like, a month.
Wait. What customshouse?

52:37.780 --> 52:38.906
Montreal.

52:41.117 --> 52:42.827
You're not pissing
in our own pool, man.

52:42.911 --> 52:45.497
You have always said you were never
gonna do a job here in Montreal.

52:45.581 --> 52:48.251
- I know. I know. Can you do it?
- Steven!

52:48.293 --> 52:50.128
Who are you talking to
at this hour?

52:50.170 --> 52:54.341
I am having a fucking conversation
with a friend of mine, Mother!

52:55.133 --> 52:58.638
- Are you... Are you okay?
- She is a ghoul.

52:58.721 --> 53:01.141
Now, tell me
exactly what you want.

53:01.224 --> 53:05.187
Just one second. Here's someone
who can tell you what we need.

53:05.270 --> 53:07.648
Just tell him what you need.

53:07.731 --> 53:10.985
I need separate disarm and reset
master codes for the whole system...

53:11.026 --> 53:13.405
and I need the individual
sector bypass codes...

53:13.488 --> 53:17.076
so I can shut down one zone without
lighting off the whole board.

53:17.159 --> 53:19.203
- Okay?
- Yes.

53:20.997 --> 53:22.456
- You got that?
- Got it.

53:22.540 --> 53:25.127
Now, listen, I'm gonna
need this within 48 hours.

53:25.169 --> 53:27.004
If you do that,
I'll double your last price.

53:27.963 --> 53:30.675
Dude, give me a Kaypro 64
and a live dial tone...

53:30.758 --> 53:33.010
and I can do anything.

53:34.971 --> 53:37.892
Oh, now you are going to die.

53:39.310 --> 53:41.813
This is someone you work with?

53:41.854 --> 53:44.107
And you're giving me
a hard time.

54:15.059 --> 54:18.522
Thursday, 8:07a.m.

54:18.605 --> 54:21.567
Hi. I got your message.
One of the stewardesses is sick...

54:21.650 --> 54:24.779
so I have to cover for her
on a New York run.

54:24.862 --> 54:27.699
We have to talk when I come
through in a couple of days.

54:27.740 --> 54:29.702
Okay? Bye.

54:30.911 --> 54:32.830
End of messages.

54:42.842 --> 54:45.511
Just lock it.

54:45.595 --> 54:49.015
- You work here?
- No. Here.

54:57.025 --> 54:59.069
Come on.

54:59.152 --> 55:01.113
Come on.
Come on in.

55:16.881 --> 55:18.799
Want some coffee?

55:24.348 --> 55:28.019
Jeez. Is this
what we're dealing with?

55:32.399 --> 55:34.276
Page 720.

55:38.740 --> 55:43.787
- Where can I get one of these?
- You gotta know the right people.

55:43.870 --> 55:46.749
Traeger floor safe.
Here it is.

55:47.542 --> 55:50.462
Solid steel body.

55:50.545 --> 55:52.922
Filled door
with aluminum and cobalt.

55:53.840 --> 55:56.885
Half-inch hard plate.
Double dial.

55:58.721 --> 56:00.962
You're gonna need two,
three hours to drill through that.

56:00.974 --> 56:03.769
- You can't drill this.
- Why not?

56:03.852 --> 56:07.147
'Cause this is a newer model
and it's got these glass packs.

56:07.231 --> 56:10.526
See the glass pack here? See?

56:10.609 --> 56:13.780
Drill through that, the glass breaks
and those bolts spring into place.

56:13.864 --> 56:15.616
You're fucked. They're locked.
Forget it.

56:15.657 --> 56:17.952
You can't break it
with a bulldozer.

56:17.993 --> 56:20.621
I've never seen anything like that.
What do you have in mind?

56:20.704 --> 56:23.750
I don't know, but if somebody
built it, somebody can unbuild it.

56:34.804 --> 56:37.808
Yeah, see, when I shut this down,
you'll see this light go off...

56:37.850 --> 56:40.394
but up in the booth,
nothing will register.

56:43.731 --> 56:46.359
- Is that your box?
- That's it.

56:46.443 --> 56:48.445
That's a fucking monster.
That's three times the size of this.

56:48.528 --> 56:50.114
Even bigger than that.

56:50.156 --> 56:53.451
See that over there?

56:53.493 --> 56:56.496
You can see it better over here.

56:56.580 --> 56:59.624
That's an active infrared post.

56:59.666 --> 57:01.752
I don't know.
That wasn't on the system specs.

57:01.835 --> 57:05.257
That's gotta be some independent
loop they set up just in the cage.

57:06.216 --> 57:08.176
I'll take care of it.

57:14.225 --> 57:19.273
All right, just calm down, okay?
I'll be over in a few minutes.

57:20.274 --> 57:22.693
I gotta take care of something.
I'll drop you off.

57:47.847 --> 57:50.058
My mom's only out
for about a half an hour.

57:55.315 --> 57:58.777
I was cruising around Ironclad's
server at the root COBOL level...

57:58.860 --> 58:03.782
when someone counter-cracked me,
hacked into my machines, my data.

58:03.865 --> 58:05.701
For three minutes,
I was fully exposed.

58:05.784 --> 58:10.123
Now I have to fire wall my whole
operations all from scratch.

58:10.207 --> 58:13.752
- Can you tell me that in English?
- Sorry.

58:13.836 --> 58:16.714
I was a few keystrokes away from
pulling those engineering codes...

58:16.797 --> 58:18.925
when I bump into a guy
on the other end.

58:19.009 --> 58:21.845
- And what's on the other end?
- Ironclad's computers.

58:21.887 --> 58:24.056
My guess is he's some
low-level systems administrator.

58:24.139 --> 58:29.270
So, we switch to a private
chat room, and he sends me this.

58:31.189 --> 58:32.107
Can you believe that?

58:32.191 --> 58:35.361
The guy comes into my world
and calls me an asshole.

58:35.403 --> 58:38.489
- Can you get me the bypass codes?
- I type, " How much?" He types...

58:38.573 --> 58:40.366
" Engineering codes for
the customshouse basement?"

58:40.450 --> 58:42.535
I say, "You guessed it,
Blue's Clues."

58:42.577 --> 58:44.664
And he says, " Fuck you."
And I say, " No, fuck you."

58:44.747 --> 58:47.416
And he says, " No, fuck you."
I'm like, " No, fuck you."

58:47.500 --> 58:49.419
Then he's like, " No, fuck..."

58:49.460 --> 58:52.005
Can you get me the bypass codes?

58:53.256 --> 58:57.052
The guy wants 50 thou
in exchange for the codes.

58:57.135 --> 59:00.056
- Fifty thousand.
- Yes.

59:02.726 --> 59:04.144
Get the account number.

59:04.227 --> 59:06.313
I'll wire the money, and he'll
deliver the codes through you.

59:06.396 --> 59:07.898
Negative.
The guy won't go for a transfer.

59:07.981 --> 59:10.402
He wants cash
and he wants to do it in person.

59:11.736 --> 59:13.447
- Anything else?
- No.

59:13.530 --> 59:16.492
You set it up.
I'll let myself out.

59:16.575 --> 59:19.620
When this score's done, I'm gonna
brute this creep with everything.

59:19.703 --> 59:23.333
By the time I'm done with this fuck,
he won't be able to hide in Bolivia!

59:51.991 --> 59:55.120
Jesus.
Look at all these people.

59:55.161 --> 59:58.081
Who sets up a meeting
in a public park?

01:00:02.170 --> 01:00:04.965
- You see him?
- Still looking.

01:00:19.982 --> 01:00:23.402
Got him.
He brought backup.

01:00:25.029 --> 01:00:27.032
Okay, I got him.

01:00:39.880 --> 01:00:42.675
Hey, how ya doing?
Good to see ya.

01:00:42.717 --> 01:00:45.803
Shake my hand. That's right.
You my guy?

01:00:45.887 --> 01:00:47.096
Yeah.

01:00:47.180 --> 01:00:50.308
- Who's this?
- Cousin.

01:00:50.392 --> 01:00:54.021
Cousin? Okay. See the guy
over my left shoulder...

01:00:54.063 --> 01:00:59.277
back there on the bench,
reading the paper, the big one?

01:00:59.361 --> 01:01:02.906
That's my cousin, okay?

